Welcome to Agros 2D.

This manual is intended to Debian-based systems. For other systems is very similar.

Requirements
============

You must first install the needed requirements:
- Hermes2D (http://www.hpfem.org/hermes2d), '
- Nokia Qt 4.5 (http://www.qtsoftware.com/products), 
- Qwt 5.0 (http://qwt.sourceforge.net) and 
- Triangle (http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~quake/triangle.html).

Install the required libraries:

$ sudo apt-get install libqt4-dev qt4-dev-tools libsuitesparse-dev libqwt5-qt4-dev libtriangle-1.6

Hermes2D is not available in debian repositories and you have to compile it from source. 
You can also use simplified dpkg-buildpackage way.

To compile Agros 2D you need qmake, and g++, install this packages:

$ sudo apt-get install qmake g++

Documentation
=============

Agros 2D manual is available from the program by pressing F1 or from main menu. This help can be generated by running:

qhelpgenerator ./doc/help/agros2d.qhp -o ./doc/help/agros2d.qch

or using prepared script with parameter

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -h

Localization
============

Agros 2D is available in two languages (Czech and English). Files with localization can be genarated by running:

lrelease ./lang/*.ts ./lang/*.qm

or using prepared script with parameter

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -l

Compilation
===========

The application can by compiled by running:

$ qmake agros2d.pro
$ make

or using prepared script with parameter

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -c

Binary package can be build by running:

dpkg-buildpackage -sgpg -rfakeroot

or using prepared script with parameter

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -p

Tips
====

To simplify the described steps (documentation and localization generation and building a package) run:

$ ./agros2d.debian.sh -a

